            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target thickness is limited by the maximum range",
                " of these products in the target material. 25*25 mm2",
                " U-238, thickness 15-mg/cm**2, was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".A large coaxial Ge-detector, 76% relative",
                " efficiency, gated by beta-particles passing through a",
                " thin plastic scintillator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-C12"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The carbon target for converting the deuteron",
                " beam into neutrons had a thickness of 1.54 g/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Broad neutron spectrum in the range of 90 degree.",
                " Mean energy 20 MeV, full width at half maximum",
                " aprx.30 MeV - from Fig.1 of EPJ/A,9,385"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.For each observable activity in a given",
                "  mass chain, peak area were corrected for detection",
                "  efficiency and decay branching of the corresponding",
                "  transitions in order to obtain the number of decay."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.In order to obtain an independent",
                " measurement, was counted gamma-rays of activated",
                " foils of Al, thickness 0.27-g/cm**2 and Co, thickness",
                " 0.67-g/cm**2, placed downstream of the converter",
                " instead of the U-target. Firstly, knowing the deuteron",
                " beam intensity, activated foil thickness and the",
                " measured gamma-ray rates one determines a combined",
                " experimental cross-section-sigma(C). Secondly, one can",
                " calculate an effective cross-section-sigma(N) for",
                " neutron activation of the foils, which takes into",
                " account the angular and energy distributions of the",
                " neutrons impinging on the foils. Comparison of sigma(N",
                " with sigma(C) gives the N/d-conversion factor."
              ]
            }
          ],
